						               													<description>Solve one more case, an independent scenario called Suburbia. It will allow you to delve deep into the Cleveland suburbs and face corruption at its finest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Suburbia is a great way to familiarize yourself with the rules of the game and fully prepare yourself for the demanding campaign from the box. But it is also a perfect scenario for a one-off game session. It is a bit shorter and simpler than the other missions, thus we also recommend playing it with friends who are not convinced to devote more than 15 hours to the entire campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Suburbia is a standalone case for Detective: A Modern Crime Board Game, previously available only for those, who pre-ordered the game. Now you can play it using files available on Portal Games official website. &amp;#10;You will need a base game to play this scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: The original Print and Play of this case was stand alone, the physical printing requires the base game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
